Title: A Certain Hunger
Author: Chelsea G. Summers
My Review: I was expecting a "good for her" novel and it ended up being a "I feel so bad for them" novel. It just feels like the main character is trying SO hard to shock us that everything else kinda gets lost in the sauce. The only part that I enjoyed was towards the end when she actually fell in love - the description was beautiful, but then BOOM there she goes trying to sell this "I don't care I'm a psycopath" narrative again
